HEADWORD: Cragsman
<hw>Crags"man</hw> <pr>(kr⟦acr⟧gz"m⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Cragsmen</plw> <pr>(-m⟦eit⟧n)</pr>.</plu>
<def>One accustomed to climb rocks or crags; esp., one who makes a
business of climbing the cliffs overhanging the sea to get the eggs of
sea birds or the birds themselves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Craie</ent>⟦br⟧
